    {
      "id": "p009",
      "index": 9,
      "source": "In grating couplers (GCs), light enters from the top and the fiber is positioned at a small angle above the grating. As the light reaches the grating, the periodic structure scatters and bends the light downward into the waveguides.",
      "source_html": null,
      "element_type": "p",
      "inline_elements": [],
      "parent_block_id": "b0255",
      "parent_block_index": 255,
      "parent_block_type": "p",
      "parent_block_markdown": "In grating couplers (GCs), light enters from the top and the fiber is positioned at a small angle above the grating. As the light reaches the grating, the periodic structure scatters and bends the light downward into the waveguides.",
      "parent_block_plain_text": "In grating couplers (GCs), light enters from the top and the fiber is positioned at a small angle above the grating. As the light reaches the grating, the periodic structure scatters and bends the light downward into the waveguides.",
      "parent_source_html": null,
      "parent_inline_elements": [],
      "segment_start": 0,
      "segment_end": 232,
      "expected_tokens": [],
      "format_recovery_status": "not_applicable",
      "format_errors": [],
      "is_heading": false,
      "heading_level": null,
      "heading_chain": [],
      "is_metadata": false,
      "metadata_type": null,
      "translations": {
        "pro": {
          "text": "在光栅耦合器（GC）中，光从顶部入射，光纤以较小角度置于光栅上方。当光到达光栅时，周期性结构会将光散射并向下弯折，进入波导。",
          "model": "pro",
          "created_at": "2026-04-22T18:22:11.403325",
          "tokenized_text": null,
          "format_issues": []
        }
      },
      "confirmed": null,
