    {
      "id": "p010",
      "index": 10,
      "source": "The major benefit of grating/vertical coupling is the ability to have multiple rows of fibers, allowing more fibers per optical engine. GCs also do not need to be placed at the bottom of the substrate, making it possible to place the OE on the interposer. Lastly, GC does not need to be positioned with extreme precision and it can be more easily manufactured with a simple two-step etched process. The drawbacks of GC is that single-polarization grating couplers only work for a limited range of wavelengths and are highly polarization sensitive.",
      "source_html": null,
      "element_type": "p",
      "inline_elements": [],
      "parent_block_id": "b0256",
      "parent_block_index": 256,
      "parent_block_type": "p",
      "parent_block_markdown": "The major benefit of grating/vertical coupling is the ability to have multiple rows of fibers, allowing more fibers per optical engine. GCs also do not need to be placed at the bottom of the substrate, making it possible to place the OE on the interposer. Lastly, GC does not need to be positioned with extreme precision and it can be more easily manufactured with a simple two-step etched process. The drawbacks of GC is that single-polarization grating couplers only work for a limited range of wavelengths and are highly polarization sensitive.",
      "parent_block_plain_text": "The major benefit of grating/vertical coupling is the ability to have multiple rows of fibers, allowing more fibers per optical engine. GCs also do not need to be placed at the bottom of the substrate, making it possible to place the OE on the interposer. Lastly, GC does not need to be positioned with extreme precision and it can be more easily manufactured with a simple two-step etched process. The drawbacks of GC is that single-polarization grating couplers only work for a limited range of wavelengths and are highly polarization sensitive.",
      "parent_source_html": null,
      "parent_inline_elements": [],
      "segment_start": 0,
      "segment_end": 547,
      "expected_tokens": [],
      "format_recovery_status": "not_applicable",
      "format_errors": [],
      "is_heading": false,
      "heading_level": null,
      "heading_chain": [],
      "is_metadata": false,
      "metadata_type": null,
      "translations": {
        "pro": {
          "text": "光栅/垂直耦合的主要优势在于能够布置多排光纤，从而使单个光引擎（OE）容纳更多光纤。光栅耦合器（GC）无需置于基板底部，因此可将光引擎（OE）放置在中介层上。最后，光栅耦合无需极高定位精度，且可通过简单的两步刻蚀工艺更轻松地实现制造。其缺点是，单偏振光栅耦合器的工作波长范围有限，且对偏振高度敏感。",
          "model": "pro",
          "created_at": "2026-04-22T18:22:11.403353",
          "tokenized_text": null,
